# Example /etc/fstab entries for Chapter 5 exercises
# ALWAYS use UUID= instead of device paths like /dev/sdb1
#
# Format: <device>  <mountpoint>  <type>  <options>  <dump>  <fsck>
#
# Regular XFS mount:
# UUID=xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx  /mnt/data  xfs  defaults  0 0
#
# LVM logical volume (also use UUID):
# UUID=xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx  /mnt/appdata  xfs  defaults  0 0
#
# LUKS encrypted device (requires matching /etc/crypttab entry):
# /dev/mapper/secret  /mnt/secret  xfs  defaults  0 0
#
# Mount options explained:
#   defaults    = rw,suid,dev,exec,auto,nouser,async
#   noatime     = don't update access times (improves performance)
#   nofail      = don't fail boot if device is missing
#   x-systemd.device-timeout=30  = wait 30s for device to appear
#
# The last two fields:
#   dump (5th) = 0 means don't back up with dump utility
#   fsck (6th) = 0 means don't check at boot (XFS uses xfs_repair, not fsck)
#                1 for root filesystem, 2 for other ext4 filesystems
